1. Declare Material UI Theme in themes.xml 
--> parent="Theme.Material3.DayNight.NoActionBar"

2. Always try Material UI Follow Up for better UI-UX from start of the App 
--> <a href="https://m3.material.io/components">Material UI</a>

3. Use Glide for Image Processing 
--> https://bumptech.github.io/glide/doc/download-setup.html

4. Always use Constraint Layout for better management of child views 
--> Always use constraints for child views

5. Use Splash API for Splash Screen 
--> https://developer.android.com/develop/ui/views/launch/splash-screen

6. Use MVVM Architecture for better management of Project Work

7. Use Retrofit for network request 
--> https://square.github.io/retrofit/

8. Always manage exception for better App Stability in Any Condition
--> try/catch, switching between threads whenever needed

9. Use Network Receiver for better management of Network Related Project

10. Use Live Data while communicating with API for better management of Exception
--> https://developer.android.com/jetpack/androidx/releases/lifecycle

11. Avoid recursive functions in project 
--> Allow max two try then display fail to do task message

12. Use Navigation Jetpack for better management of Fragments
--> https://developer.android.com/guide/navigation/integrations/ui
--> https://developer.android.com/jetpack/androidx/releases/navigation

13. Follow API Request Structure
--> ViewModel - Repository - Interface

14. Use Room Database for Local Database
--> Structure : ViewModel - Repository - Interface
--> https://developer.android.com/training/data-storage/room

15. Always Use Parcelize Model
--> https://developer.android.com/kotlin/parcelize#kts

16. Use Coroutine for long running tasks
--> https://developer.android.com/kotlin/coroutines

17. BlurView
--> https://github.com/Dimezis/BlurView